@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home Page";
}

<!-- Welcome section -->
<div class="text-center">
    <h1 class="display-4">Welcome to Our Zoo</h1>
    <p class="lead">Discover the amazing world of animals at our zoo. We are home to a diverse range of species, each with their own unique characteristics and habitats. Explore our zoo to learn more about these incredible creatures and the efforts we make to conserve and protect them.</p>
    <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" asp-controller="Animals" asp-action="Index">Go to Animals Page</a>
</div>

<!-- About Us section -->
<div class="mt-4">
    <h2>About Us</h2>
    <p>This website was created by Hieu Phan & Abdelaziz Anime for our school, Windesheim. Our goal is to provide an engaging and educational platform for visitors to learn about the diverse range of animals in our zoo.</p>
    <p>We hope you enjoy exploring the site and discovering the fascinating world of animals.</p>
</div>

<!-- Features section -->
<div class="mt-4">
    <h2>What You Can Do on This Website</h2>
    <p>Our website offers a variety of features to help you explore and manage the zoo:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>View Animals:</strong> Browse through our extensive list of animals to learn more about each species, their habitats, and their unique characteristics.</li>
        <li><strong>Create New Animals:</strong> Add new animals to the zoo's database, complete with detailed information about their species, dietary needs, and more.</li>
        <li><strong>Edit Animal Information:</strong> Update the details of existing animals to ensure the information is accurate and up-to-date.</li>
        <li><strong>Delete Animals:</strong> Remove animals from the database if they are no longer part of the zoo.</li>
        <li><strong>View Enclosures:</strong> Explore the different enclosures in the zoo and see which animals are housed in each one.</li>
        <li><strong>Create New Enclosures:</strong> Add new enclosures to the zoo, specifying the type of habitat and the animals that will be housed there.</li>
        <li><strong>Edit Enclosure Information:</strong> Update the details of existing enclosures to reflect any changes or improvements.</li>
        <li><strong>Delete Enclosures:</strong> Remove enclosures from the database if they are no longer in use.</li>
        <li><strong>Read Detailed Information:</strong> Access detailed information about each animal and enclosure, including their ID, name, species, dietary class, activity pattern, and more.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<!-- Interesting Facts section -->
<div class="mt-4">
    <h2>Interesting Facts About Zoos</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Zoos play a crucial role in the conservation of endangered species. Many zoos participate in breeding programs to help increase the population of threatened animals.</li>
        <li>The first modern zoo, the Vienna Zoo, was founded in 1752 and is still operating today.</li>
        <li>Zoos provide educational programs and exhibits to help the public learn about wildlife and the importance of conservation.</li>
        <li>Many zoos have research programs that contribute to our understanding of animal behavior, genetics, and health.</li>
        <li>Zoos often have enrichment programs to keep animals mentally and physically stimulated, which is essential for their well-being.</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<!-- Visit Our Zoo section -->
<div class="mt-4">
    <h2>Visit Our Zoo</h2>
    <p>We invite you to visit our zoo and experience the wonders of the animal kingdom firsthand. Whether you're interested in learning about exotic species or simply enjoying a day out with family and friends, our zoo has something for everyone.</p>
</div>





